Hi guys! Can't help with this module (in an email template).
As I send the email (the contact has model 2 and color 1), the result is always:
&lt;img src="https://www.orbitalwaves.it/.jpg" alt="Model 2 - Color 1" width="800" height="300"/&gt;
Seems the contact fields are right and the output of the macro don't work as expected.
I tried to force
{% set contact = {
  "pick_your_color": "Color 1",
  "pick_your_model": "Model 3"
}
%}
to test the macro and everything works as expected.
If I get rid of the macros and I just use plain for, I get the same weird behaviour.

Same issue with this alternative code

{% set colors = [
    {"code":"a", "name":"Color 1"},
    {"code":"b", "name":"Color 2"},
    {"code":"c", "name":"Color 3"}
]
%}
{% set models = [
    {"code":"01", "name":"Model 1"},
    {"code":"02", "name":"Model 2"},
    {"code":"03", "name":"Model 3"},
]
%}

Model: {{ models|selectattr('name','equalto',contact.pick_your_model)|first|attr('code') }}
Color: {{ colors|selectattr('name','equalto',contact.pick_your_color)|first|attr('code') }}
